{"id":220848162,"title":"Infinite Sparse Factor Analysis and Infinite Independent Components Analysis","authors":["David A. Knowles","Zoubin Ghahramani"],"_abstract":"ABSTRACT A nonparametric Bayesian extension of Independent Components Analysis (ICA) is proposed where observed data Y is modelled as a linear superposition, G, of a potentially infinite number of hidden sources, X. Whether a given source is active for a specific data point is specified by an infinite binary matrix, Z. The resulting sparse representation allows increased data reduction compared to standard ICA. We define a prior on Z using the Indian Buffet Process (IBP). We describe four variants of the model, with Gaussian or Laplacian priors on X and the one or two-parameter IBPs. We demonstrate Bayesian inference under these models using a Markov Chain Monte Carlo (MCMC) algorithm on synthetic and gene expression data and compare to standard ICA algorithms.","cited_in":[{"id":260623423,"url":"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/260623423_Compressed_Sensing-Based_Inpainting_of_Aqua_Moderate_Resolution_Imaging_Spectroradiometer_Band_6_Using_Adaptive_Spectrum-Weighted_Sparse_Bayesian_Dictionary_Learning"},{"id":230996489,"url":"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/230996489_A_Bayesian_Nonparametric_Approach_to_Image_Super-Resolution"},{"id":239938718,"url":"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/239938718_Bayesian_Unification_of_Sound_Source_Localization_and_Separation_with_Permutation_Resolution"},{"id":51948589,"url":"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/51948589_Distance_Dependent_Infinite_Latent_Feature_Models"},{"id":224246550,"url":"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/224246550_Covariate-dependent_dictionary_learning_and_sparse_coding"},{"id":47843669,"url":"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/47843669_Nonparametric_Bayesian_sparse_factor_models_with_application_to_geneexpression_modeling"},{"id":227113488,"url":"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/227113488_Bayesia